				  agentsmith

		      Copyright (c) 2010 Rafael Ostertag


agentsmith  is  a  daemon  that  monitors  a  log  file  for  remote  break-in
attempts. It uses  a user customizable regular expression  to identify break-in
attempts and calls a script or other suitable application upon detection.

For more information refer to the man pages.

Dependencies
------------

agentsmith is known to work on Solaris 10, OpenSolaris, FreeBSD, OpenBSD, and
Linux.

It  requires a  more  or  less recent  version  of the  PCRE  library which  is
available from http://www.pcre.org.


Installation
------------

Refer to the INSTALL file


Examples
--------

After building agentsmith,the example/ directory holds examples for

 * action scripts (this is what gets executed if a break-in attempt is
   detected)

 * configuration file (agentsmith.conf.example)

 * init.d start script (agentsmith)

 * Solaris SMF Manifest (agentsmith.xml)


